The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Lawsuits pile up in US
                                                                                                               Lawsuits pile up in US
                            
	New York, Jan. 11 (PTI): About a dozen lawsuits have been filed against Satyam Computer Services in the US courts charging the Indian IT firm with duping thousands of American investors of billions of dollars.        
	On the specific damages sought in the lawsuit, law firm Vianale amp; Vianale LLPs counsel Keneth J. Vianale said the sum duped could be in hundreds of millions of dollars. In cases of this sort, it is not unusual for the damages to be in the hundreds of millions of dollars, he said.         
	Another law firm Pomerantz Haudek Block Grossman amp; Gross said it has commenced an investigation of the scandal on behalf of investor clients, and is exploring the possible claims that can be raised.                                                                                                                                        
